"{\"uid\": \"si.com-olympics-2024-01-01-nbc-add-snoop-dogg-reporter-for-paris-olympics-coverage\", \"text\": \"Ahead of the 2024 Summer Olympics in Paris, NBC is turning to an unlikely source to provide commentary.  Celebrity musician Snoop Dogg will serve as a prime-time analyst for this year\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s Olympic Games, NBC announced Sunday evening. The move follows his acclaimed streaming-only commentary of the 2020 Summer Olympics in Tokyo, provided alongside comedian Kevin Hart on Peacock.  \\u00e2\\u0080\\u009cI grew up watching the Olympics and am thrilled to see the incredible athletes bring their A-game to Paris. It\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s a celebration of skill, dedication, and the pursuit of greatness,\\u00e2\\u0080\\u009d the rapper said in astatement. \\u00e2\\u0080\\u009cWe\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099re going to have some amazing competitions and, of course, I will be bringing that Snoop style to the mix. It\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s going to be the most epic Olympics ever, so stay tuned, and keep it locked.\\u00e2\\u0080\\u009d  Snoop Dogg appeared in an advertisement for NBC\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s Olympics coverage with several American athletes during the\\u00c2Green Bay Packers\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099 33-10 win over the\\u00c2Minnesota Vikings\\u00c2\\u00a0on Sunday evening.  The opening ceremony for the Paris Olympics is currently scheduled to take place on July 26.  Loading recommendations... Please wait while we load personalized content recommendations  Patrick Andres is a staff writer on the Breaking and Trending News team at Sports Illustrated. He joined SI in December 2022, having worked for The Blade, Athlon Sports, Fear the Sword and Diamond Digest. Andres has covered everything from zero-attendance Big Ten basketball to a seven-overtime college football game. He is a graduate of Northwestern University's Medill School of Journalism with a double major in history .  \\u00c2\\u00a9 2026ABG-SI LLC-SPORTS ILLUSTRATED IS A REGISTERED TRADEMARK OF ABG-S